	h1={`The Bible for Those Facing Cancer`}
	heroEyebrow={`A Father For`}
	heroSubhead={`A diagnosis can make the ground fall out from under you — the scans, the waiting, the treatment, the fear that won't sleep. Here is the truth underneath all of it: you do not walk this valley alone. There is a Father who is near to the brokenhearted, and He will not leave your side.`}
	heroBase={`https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/472476e577dd1d4cc1e1f42776a4f7ad57245212-1100x733.jpg`}
	heroAlt={`Warm light glowing through the curtains of a quiet room`}
	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you or someone you love is facing cancer, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> The fear, the uncertainty, the exhaustion of treatment, the question of where God is in all of it — you don't have to carry any of it alone. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free — in the infusion chair, the waiting room, or the long hours of the night — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "Bible verses for cancer," "verses for strength," "healing," or "comfort for cancer patients and caregivers," the answer starts in one place: even in the valley, you are not alone. Your Father is near.`}
	keyTakeaway={`Cancer is one of the loneliest valleys a person can walk — but you do not walk it alone. The Father who is near to the brokenhearted holds you through every scan, every treatment, and every fear, and He promises He will never leave your side.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight cancer carries`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you feel afraid, exhausted, or like the fear never fully lets go — of you or of the people walking with you — you are not weak and you are not alone. Millions are walking this same road, and the numbers say it out loud.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `2 million+`, label: `new cancer cases are expected to be diagnosed in the U.S. this year (American Cancer Society, Cancer Facts & Figures 2024)` },
		{ value: `18 million+`, label: `cancer survivors are living in the United States today — a number that keeps rising (National Cancer Institute)` },
		{ value: `~69%`, label: `5-year relative survival rate across all cancers, up from about 49% in the mid-1970s (NCI SEER)` },
		{ value: `Up to 1 in 4`, label: `people with cancer experience clinical depression, and many more live with ongoing anxiety (National Cancer Institute)` },
		{ value: `~53 million`, label: `family caregivers in the U.S. provide unpaid care for loved ones, many of them facing serious illness like cancer (AARP & NAC, 2020)` },
		{ value: `Most patients`, label: `report that faith and spirituality help them cope with cancer and find meaning during treatment (American Cancer Society)` },
	]}
	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real person — maybe you, maybe someone you love. The phone call that split your life into before and after. The scan you wait days for the results of. The treatment that heals and exhausts in the same breath. The fear that visits at 3 a.m. when the house is quiet. And for the ones who love you — the spouse, the child, the friend — the helpless ache of walking beside someone through a valley they cannot carry for them.</p><p>None of this means your faith is failing. It means you are human, facing something no one was built to face alone. There is no shame in the fear, the tears, or the questions. There is a Father who sees every bit of it, who draws near — not far off — when your heart is broken, and who has something to say to you in the middle of the valley.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
		{ label: `American Cancer Society — Cancer Facts & Figures 2024`, url: `https://www.cancer.org/research/cancer-facts-statistics/all-cancer-facts-figures/2024-cancer-facts-figures.html` },
		{ label: `National Cancer Institute — Cancer Statistics`, url: `https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/understanding/statistics` },
		{ label: `National Cancer Institute — SEER Cancer Statistics`, url: `https://seer.cancer.gov/statistics/` },
	]}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for those facing cancer`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what no diagnosis can take from you: the answer to the valley is not a guarantee that the road will be easy, and it is not a promise that the fear will never come. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a tender, present Father who is near to the brokenhearted and walks every step of the valley at your side.</p><p>This Bible will not tell you that faith makes cancer disappear, or that you only need to believe hard enough to be healed. That is not the Father's heart, and it is not the truth. What it tells you is deeper and steadier: that even as you walk through the darkest valley, you do not walk it alone — your Father is <em>with</em> you, and His presence is the comfort that nothing, not even death itself, can break.</p><p>So before you are a patient, a chart, a diagnosis, or a caregiver running on empty — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the steady presence underneath the fear, the one who says: I am here. I have not left you. Lean on Me, and I will hold you through every scan, every treatment, and every night.</p>`}
