	voiceIntroHtml={`Nine Bible verses for those facing cancer in the Father's Heart Bible™ — each one a word from your Father, near to you in the valley. Tap any reference to read and listen free.`}
	verses={[
		{ ref: `Psalm 23:4`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 23, text: `Even when I walk through the darkest valley, the valley of the shadow of death, I will not be afraid — for You, my Father, are with me; Your rod and Your staff, they comfort me.`, note: `The valley is real, and so is His presence in it — you walk it with your Father beside you, not alone.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 41:10`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 41, text: `Do not be afraid, for I am with you; do not be dismayed, for I am your Father. I will strengthen you, I will help you, I will hold you up with My righteous right hand.`, note: `When fear rises before a scan or a result, hear His promise: I am with you, and I am holding you up.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 46:1`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 46, text: `Your Father is your refuge and your strength, an ever-present help in trouble.`, note: `He is not a distant help you have to reach — He is ever-present, right here in the trouble with you.` },
		{ ref: `2 Corinthians 1:3-4`, slug: `2-corinthians`, ch: 1, text: `Praise be to the Father of compassion and the God of all comfort, who comforts us in all our troubles, so that we can comfort others with the comfort we ourselves receive from Him.`, note: `Your Father is the source of all comfort — and the comfort He gives you can one day steady someone else.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 43:2`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 43, text: `When you pass through the waters, I will be with you; when you walk through the fire, you will not be burned, for I am the Lord your Father, your Savior.`, note: `He does not promise no waters and no fire — He promises to be with you in them, all the way through.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 34:18`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 34, text: `Your Father is close to the brokenhearted, and He saves those who are crushed in spirit.`, note: `On the days the weight crushes you, He does not pull back — He draws closest of all.` },
		{ ref: `Matthew 11:28`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 11, text: `Come to Me, all you who are weary and burdened, and I will give you rest, says your Father.`, note: `When treatment has drained you and you have nothing left, His invitation still stands: come, and rest in Me.` },
		{ ref: `Deuteronomy 31:8`, slug: `deuteronomy`, ch: 31, text: `The Lord your Father Himself goes before you and will be with you; He will never leave you nor forsake you. Do not be afraid; do not be discouraged.`, note: `He has already gone ahead into whatever comes next — and He will never leave you in it.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 73:26`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 73, text: `My body and my heart may fail, but God is the strength of my heart and my portion forever, says your Father.`, note: `Even when the body grows weak, He remains — the strength of your heart, and yours forever.` },
	]}
	offersHeading={`What "our Father" offers you`}
	offersIntroHtml={`Cancer takes so much sense of control. Here is what your Father gives instead — freely, because you are already His, in every part of the journey.`}
	offersBlocks={[
		{ heading: `His presence in the valley`, bodyHtml: `You do not walk the darkest valley alone: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/23" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">your Father is with you</a>, His rod and staff a comfort through every shadow, every scan, and every uncertain step.` },
		{ heading: `Strength for the weary`, bodyHtml: `When treatment has emptied you, His invitation stands: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/matthew/11" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">come to Him for rest</a> — He carries what you no longer can and renews the heart that has run out.` },
		{ heading: `Comfort for the brokenhearted`, bodyHtml: `He is the <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/2-corinthians/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father of compassion and God of all comfort</a> — close to the brokenhearted, drawing nearest on the days the weight feels heaviest.` },
		{ heading: `A presence that never leaves`, bodyHtml: `Through the waters and the fire, He does not step away: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/isaiah/43" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">He is with you</a>, going before you, promising never to leave you nor forsake you.` },
	]}
	whyHeading={`Why the Father's Heart Bible™ for those facing cancer`}
	whyBlocks={[
		{ heading: `You meet a Father near in the valley, not a distant God`, bodyHtml: `When you're afraid, the last thing you need is a God who feels far away. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a <em>Father</em> wherever Scripture does — from <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/genesis/1" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Genesis 1</a> on — so instead of a verdict from on high, you meet the One who is near to the brokenhearted and walks the valley at your side.` },
		{ heading: `It's free, with audio for infusion chairs and sleepless nights`, bodyHtml: `No account, no purchase, no app. <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Read it free online</a> with audio on every chapter — when your eyes are too tired to read, let His Word be read over you in the hospital bed, the infusion chair, or the long hours of the night.` },
		{ heading: `It speaks to the fear you're actually carrying`, bodyHtml: `Afraid? Exhausted? Wondering where God is? Start with our <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a> or learn to bring it all to Him with our <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how-to-pray guide</a> — the Word meets you right where the fear lives.` },
	]}
	voicesHeading={`The Father's heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`Even in the valley, you do not walk alone. The truth beneath every verse here, that God is before anything else a Father who is near, is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; George MacDonald, Charles Spurgeon, and Andrew Murray (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>Some days the verses will steady you, and some days you will read them through tears and feel nothing change. That's okay. The Father's nearness isn't a feeling you have to manufacture — it's a promise that holds whether you feel it or not. Every word you take in is your Father planting something in you that the fear cannot uproot.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I know the fear you carry — the waiting, the scans, the nights the worry will not quiet. And I want you to hear Me above all of it: I am with you in this valley. I have not left your side, and I will not. You do not face a single moment of this alone.</p><p>You do not have to be strong enough on your own, and you do not have to pretend you're not afraid. Bring Me the fear, the exhaustion, the questions — all of it. Lean on Me, and I will hold you up. I am near to the brokenhearted, I am the strength of your heart, and whatever comes, I am your Father, and I am here."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for those facing cancer`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we come to You for everyone facing cancer — every patient hearing hard news, every body weary from treatment, every heart heavy with fear. Draw near to them as only You can, Father of compassion and God of all comfort. Let them know, deep beneath the fear, that they are not walking this valley alone — that You are with them in the waters and the fire, holding them up with Your right hand.</p><p>Give strength to the weary and rest to the ones who have nothing left. Steady them through every scan, every waiting room, every long night. Be near to the brokenhearted, and let Your peace, the peace beyond understanding, guard their hearts and minds when the worry will not stop.</p><p>Father, we lift up the caregivers too — the spouses, the children, the friends carrying a weight they cannot put down. Sustain them, hold them, and let them feel You walking beside them. And we ask Your wisdom, skill, and compassion for the doctors, nurses, and medical teams who care for them — guide their hands and their hearts.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
